    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Here is a list of the user events we need to handle:\n1. Click on a cell in the CM editor area\n   - `unselect` other cell\n   - `select` and `focus` clicked cell\n2. Click on a cell, but not in the CM editor area\n   - `unselect` other cell\n   - `select` and clicked cell\n3. A cell is in the state `S+F` or `S+~F` and a user clicks somewhere else on the page\n   - `unselect` cell\n4. A cell is in the state `S+~F` and a user wants to use the keyboard to focus the cell (`S+F`). We currently use `Enter` in text cells for this action.\n   - `focus` cell\n5. A cell is in the `S+F` or `S+~F` states and a user hits `Shift-Enter`\n   - `unfocus` cell\n6. A cell is in the state `S+F` and up/down arrow keys are used. This needs to include the possibility that the user will navigate off the top/bottom of a cell.\n   - If off the top/bottom `unselect` curent\n   - Then `select` and `focus` next/prev\n7. A cell is in the state `~S+~F` and up/down arrow keys are used to navigate.\n   - `unselect` prev and `select` next\n"
  },
